3.30	Spokesmodel	Promotional model	A promotional model is a person hired to drive consumer demand for a product, service, brand, or concept by directly interacting with potential consumers. A vast majority of promotional model are female and typically is intended to be attractive in physical appearance. They serve to provide information about the product or service and make it appealing to consumers. While the length of interaction may be short, the promotional model delivers a live experience that reflects on the product or service he or she is representing.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9c/CBOSS_girls_%40_3GSM.jpg/220px-CBOSS_girls_%40_3GSM.jpg
